On the west side of the road, about 100 yards southwest of where the levee road crosses Big Valley Canal, in Big Valley, about 4 miles (air) northeast of the Headquarters at Ash Creek State Wildlife Area, about 7 miles (air) northeast of Bieber. T39N R08E S34 NE1/4

Ahjumawi Lava Springs State Park, 3 miles N. of McArthur, on the western edge of the Modoc Plateau. Plants collected near south end of Big Lake, the western shore, 6 feet from water edge. The Astragalus was growing among the meadow grass in an opening in the Scirpus that borders the shoreline. USGS Quadrangle: Fall River Mills 1:24,000
Local landmark: Ash Valley. Likely Quad.
